### Scenario 1: Complete Campaign Lifecycle
# Step 1: Create campaign
POST {{baseUrl}}/campaigns
Authorization: Bearer {{tenantId}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "campaign": {
    "name": "Lifecycle Test Campaign"
  }
}

# Step 2: Start the campaign (use ID from previous response)
# POST {{baseUrl}}/campaigns/{ID}/start
# Authorization: Bearer {{tenantId}}

# Step 3: Update campaign details
# PUT {{baseUrl}}/campaigns/{ID}
# Authorization: Bearer {{tenantId}}

# Step 4: Finish the campaign
# POST {{baseUrl}}/campaigns/{ID}/finish
# Authorization: Bearer {{tenantId}}

# Step 5: Verify final state
# GET {{baseUrl}}/campaigns/{ID}
# Authorization: Bearer {{tenantId}}

### Scenario 2: Multiple tenants (tenant isolation)
# Create campaign for tenant A
POST {{baseUrl}}/campaigns
Authorization: Bearer tenant-a
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "campaign": {
    "name": "Tenant A - Q1 Campaign"
  }
}

### Create campaign for tenant B
POST {{baseUrl}}/campaigns
Authorization: Bearer tenant-b
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "campaign": {
    "name": "Tenant B - Q1 Campaign"
  }
}

### List campaigns for tenant A (should only see tenant A campaigns)
GET {{baseUrl}}/campaigns
Authorization: Bearer tenant-a
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

### List campaigns for tenant B (should only see tenant B campaigns)
GET {{baseUrl}}/campaigns
Authorization: Bearer tenant-b
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

